claim.claim-text:
An antenna management method, comprising:
collecting resource use information from managed access networks;
selecting the access networks joining antenna scheduling from the managed access networks according to the resource use information to form an antenna scheduling set, wherein the access networks using the same spectrum resource form the same antenna scheduling set;
grouping wireless links of each access network in the antenna scheduling set into one or more wireless link clusters, wherein each wireless link cluster includes one or more wireless links of the same access network which have the same transmitting node or the same receiving node;
allocating wireless resources to all the wireless link clusters of the antenna scheduling set such that interference between all the wireless link clusters of the antenna scheduling set is within a predetermined range; and
sending a wireless resource allocation result to the access network in which each wireless link cluster is located.

The antenna management method of claim 2, wherein the selecting an independently-scheduling link cluster group comprises:
selecting one wireless link cluster from the wireless link clusters of the antenna scheduling set as an initial wireless link cluster of the independently-scheduling link cluster group, and setting the antenna beam of the initial wireless link cluster;
selecting a next candidate wireless link cluster to be added to the independently-scheduling link cluster group from the remaining wireless link clusters of the antenna scheduling set and setting the antenna beam of the next candidate wireless link cluster;
adding the next candidate wireless link cluster to the independently-scheduling link cluster group if the antenna beam of the next candidate wireless link cluster can be set such that the interference between the next candidate wireless link cluster and each wireless link cluster existing in the independently-scheduling link cluster group is within the predetermined range; and
repeating the selecting a next candidate wireless link cluster and setting the antenna beam of the next candidate wireless link cluster and the adding, until all the remaining wireless link clusters of the antenna scheduling set are selected and set.

The antenna management method of claim 3, wherein the allocating a bandwidth to each wireless link cluster in the independently-scheduling link cluster group comprises:
selecting the bandwidth requirement of first wireless link cluster in the independently-scheduling link cluster group at the current antenna beam setting of the first wireless link cluster as an allocation value, and allocating a bandwidth equal to the allocation value to the first wireless link cluster, wherein the first wireless link cluster is any wireless link cluster in the independently-scheduling link cluster group;
allocating to another wireless link cluster than the first wireless link cluster in the independently-scheduling link cluster group a bandwidth equal to a bandwidth requirement at the current antenna beam setting of the other wireless link cluster if the bandwidth requirement of the other wireless link cluster at the current antenna beam setting of the other wireless link cluster is lower than the allocation value;
allocating to another wireless link cluster than the first wireless link cluster in the independently-scheduling link cluster group a bandwidth equal to the allocation value if the bandwidth requirement of the other wireless link cluster at the current antenna beam setting of the other wireless link cluster is equal to or larger than the allocation value; and
subtracting the bandwidth allocated to each wireless link cluster in the independently-scheduling link cluster group at this time from the bandwidth requirement of the wireless link cluster at the current antenna beam setting of the wireless link cluster.

A computer program product on which computer readable instruction codes are stored, the instruction codes upon being read and executed by a computer causing the computer to perform an antenna management process, the antenna management process comprising:
collecting resource use information from managed access networks;
selecting the access networks joining antenna scheduling from the managed access networks according to the resource use information to form an antenna scheduling set, wherein the access networks using the same spectrum resource form the same antenna scheduling set;
